                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="illustration">405 illustrations. Another similar, complete volume held in the British
                                Library (Add. 23564), contains 453 images. This volume likely contained another 21 illustrations appeared on the missing folios at the beginning and end of this volume, 
                                with another 11 or so that adorned the replaced folios 49 to 56, so potentially 436 totalled. The majority appear of small that exemplify the early 15th
                                century style of Muzaffarid-era Shiraz.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <bindingDesc><binding notBefore="1750" notAfter="1875"><p>Rebound in Iran in a Qajar-era <hi rend="italic">mīnāyī</hi> (enamel-like) binding</p>
                            <decoNote><p>Recessed decorations features blocked central scalloped mandorlas with flanking medallions, and surrrounding margins in <material>gold</material>, with brightly painted flowers, known as <hi rend="italic">mīnāyī</hi> (enamalled) on account of the shiny appearance of the paint. For a comparable example, see Harvard University Art Museums, and references by Mihan, Bayāni, and </p></decoNote>
                                <p>
                                    
                                </p>
                        </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
